data.title: 1936 NY Times newspaper EUGENE O'NEILL wins THE NOBEL PRIZE for LITERATURE
data.meta_description: , a wistful re-imagining of his youth as he wished it had been. The following year's A Moon for the Misbegotten failed, and it was decades before coming to be considered as among his best works. This original newspaper contains a prominent front page headline, photos, and long detailed coverage ofUS Author EUGENE O'NEILL winning the 1936 Nobel Prize for Literature.
